parties.raw_snippet: This Sponsored Research and License Agreement (this “Agreement”) is entered into on November 28, 2018 (the “Effective Date”), by and between ArTara, Inc. located at 1 Little West 12th Street, New York, NY 10014 (“ArTara”), and The University of Iowa, located at c/o Division of Sponsored Programs, 2 Gilmore Hall, Iowa City, IA 52242 (“University”).
parties.reasoning: The quoted paragraph at the start of the Agreement explicitly names the contracting entities and their defined short names (“ArTara” and “University”), identifying them as the Parties to the Agreement.

contract_type.reasoning: The document title and the substance show ArTara funds and sponsors research (payments, Project phases) and obtains exclusive license/right-of-reference to University Program Data for regulatory filings and commercialization. The primary economic substance is granting ArTara licensing and regulatory rights to use Program Data to support product approvals, so the agreement is best classified as a License Agreement.

notice_period.reasoning: The contract contains termination-at-will notice provisions (e.g., 30 days to terminate) but contains no language about automatic renewal or a notice period required to prevent automatic renewal. Therefore there is no 'notice period to terminate renewal' specified.

expiration_date.reasoning: The agreement does not state a fixed expiration date or an explicit term (it contains termination rights but no explicit contract term length or 'perpetual' language). Therefore no expiration/term statement is present to extract.

renewal_term.reasoning: There is no provision describing automatic renewal or any renewal term. Renewal is not addressed, so no renewal term can be extracted.
